<LocalizedProperties><Language>en</Language><Title>Security Update for .NET Framework 3.5.1 on Windows 7 and Windows Server 2008 R2 for x64-based Systems (KB2478661)
</Title><Description>A security issue has been identified that could allow an attacker to compromise your Windows-based system that is running the Microsoft .NET Framework and gain complete control over it. You can help protect your computer by installing this update from Microsoft. After you install this item, you may have to restart your computer.</Description><UninstallNotes>This software update can be removed by selecting View installed updates in the Programs and Features Control Panel.</UninstallNotes><MoreInfoUrl>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=211423</MoreInfoUrl><SupportUrl>http://support.microsoft.com</SupportUrl></LocalizedProperties>